We have a Swing wrapper class which has a instance level boolean.  This class
also has an inner class.  When the inner class tries to access the parent class,
it gets null references to anything in the parent class (including 'this'). 
This should be allowed.  It worked in previous 2.x versions of eclipse using a
variety of JREs.

While debugging and evaluating the boolean in question, we get an entry in the
.log file and the error: Exception processing async thread queue

This is repeatable with any number of different JREs (IBM 1.4.2, IBM 1.4.1, SUN
1.5.1...).

IDE info:
eclipse platform Version: 3.0.2.1, Build id: 200503110845.
JDT Version: 3.0.2, Build id: 200503110845

Example code: 

import javax.swing.JTextField;
import javax.swing.text.Document;

public class OuterClass {

    //private boolean isSet;
    //private boolean isSet = false;
    public boolean isSet = false;

    public OuterClass() {

    }

    public class InnerClass extends JTextField {
        public InnerClass(int columns){
            super(columns);
        }
        public void setDocument(Document value) {
            super.setDocument(value);

            //runtime nullpointer happens here                       
            //error Exception processing async thread queue

            //System.out.println("isSet="+isSet);

            if (!isSet) { 
                fireActionPerformed();
            }
        }
    }

    private void doSomething() {
        isSet = true;
        JTextField textField = new InnerClass(10);
        textField.setText("");
        isSet = false;        
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        OuterClass outerClass = new OuterClass();
        outerClass.doSomething();
    }
}


